This paper proposes a value iteration algorithm for Markov decision processes (MDPs) using algebraic decision diagrams (ADDs) to represent value functions and policies. The paper focuses on large MDPs, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of Bayesian networks and dynamic programming also suggests that it may belong to the Data Mining (cs.DM) or Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on decision making and planning suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
